{"pageProps":{"articles":[{"slug":"the-state-of-web3-game-developer-tooling","title":"The State of Web3 Game Developer Tooling","featured":false,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1344px) 100vw, 1344px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1699353352-leonardo_diffusion_a_scifi_fantasy_fun_exciting_mmo_video_game_0.jpg?auto=format","width":1344,"height":752,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"","topics":[{"name":"Developer Tools"},{"name":"Web3"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-07-17","author":{"name":"Ben Naylor","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1697119847-recc1ci7md6trijcx.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/png;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"how-blockchain-gaming-founders-should-think-about-user-acquisition","title":"How Blockchain Gaming Founders Should Think About User Acquisition","featured":true,"heroImage":null,"excerpt":"Though the rise of web3 and blockchain technologies has created many opportunities for new approaches to game design, games development, and digital asset ownership, when it comes to user acquisition (UA) the fundamental problem to be solved remains unchanged: maximizing player lifetime value (LTV) while minimizing customer acquisition costs (CAC).","topics":[{"name":"Gaming"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-05-24","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"the-zkevm-the-next-frontier-of-web3-gaming","title":"The zkEVM – The Next Frontier of Web3 Gaming","featured":true,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1684936628-light-speed.jpg?auto=format","width":1920,"height":1080,"alt":null,"title":"Light Speed Image","base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>Ethereum currently has the strongest network effects of any smart contract layer 1 blockchain. Relative to other blockchain ecosystems, Ethereum has more developers, tooling and infrastructure. Despite its limitations, it continues to be a popular choice for founders looking to build games, NFTs, and Metaverse dapps. If these are going to become an integral part of our lives, the underlying infrastructure has to be extremely secure, resilient and resistant to bad actors.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Gaming"},{"name":"Web3"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-04-01","author":{"name":"Ben Naylor","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1697119847-recc1ci7md6trijcx.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/png;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"moving-on-up-exploring-the-move-smart-contract-language","title":"Moving On Up: Exploring the Move Smart Contract Language","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685005578-move-new-1.png?auto=format","width":512,"height":256,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>The Move whitepaper was first published in 2018 at Facebook as part of the Diem project. It laid out a novel approach for securely creating digital assets centered around native scarcity and access control. Its semantics are inspired by Rust, and it aims to address the issues and short-comings the designers identified in the available languages at the time (both smart contract specific and general purpose). This article will explore some of Moves features, components and tools, how they compare with existing smart contract languages, and what this new ecosystem could mean for the Web3 gaming space.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Web3"},{"name":"Gaming"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-24","author":{"name":"Ben Naylor","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1697119847-recc1ci7md6trijcx.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/png;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"pursuing-the-holy-grail-of-web3-game-interoperability","title":"Pursuing the Holy Grail of Web3 Game Interoperability","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685007358-rp1-1.jpg?auto=format","width":1920,"height":1080,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>Interoperability is a bit of a buzz word in Web3 circles, but what is its definition in practice, its practical applications, and what are Web3 builders leveraging it to achieve? Interoperability can have different meanings depending on the context. For instance, in the traditional gaming space, games can be interoperable across platforms, e.g., launching on Xbox, Playstation and PC. Within the Web3 space, there exists the notion of cross-chain interoperability, which allows assets to traverse multiple different blockchains, usually via bridge contracts. Another type of interoperability unique to Web3 is that of cross-application interoperable or portable game assets. The underlying substrate that is the blockchain in theory allows assets (NFTs or fungible tokens) to have utility in any of the applications built on top of it. Many Web3 gamers envision being able to take their in-game characters/items earned or crafted in one game and use them in another game.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Gaming"},{"name":"Web3"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-21","author":{"name":"Ben Naylor","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1697119847-recc1ci7md6trijcx.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/png;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"is-vr-making-a-comeback-again-spoiler-it-never-left","title":"Is VR making a comeback again? Spoiler: It never left","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685007511-picture-1.png?auto=format","width":936,"height":526,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>There has been no shortage of VR news of late – Meta announced Quest Pro; Bytedance launched Pico 4, pricing it to compete with Quest 2; Sony is expecting to launch 2 million PSVR2 units on 22 Feb 2023; Apple is reportedly developing three headsets to be announced in 2023 (although Apple VR rumors have been around since 2014); On the AR front, Microsoft’s Hololens and Magic Leap&nbsp;have also seen new releases this year.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Immersive Technology"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-20","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"bringing-your-whole-selves-online-the-present-and-future-of-avatars","title":"Bringing Your Whole Selves Online: The Present and Future of Avatars","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1908px) 100vw, 1908px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685007853-epic-games_metahuman-creator_header_bw_jpg.jpg?auto=format","width":1908,"height":1080,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>Why Avatars Matter. What do you look like on the internet? Answering this simple question is trickier than it may seem. That’s because your digital identity is most likely split between different places — each of them, its own world, with distinct rules and limited possibilities when it comes to self-representation. Technical constraints aside, how you present yourself to the world also depends on who you’re talking to. LinkedIn you might understandably look more serious than Instagram you, donning formal attire instead of a boxy T-shirt: to each social graph, a certain facet of your personality.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Immersive Technology"},{"name":"Web3"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-17","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"bitkraft-summit-2022","title":"BITKRAFT Summit 2022","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008072-bitkraft-monday-002-1-scaled.jpg?auto=format","width":2560,"height":1707,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>After an extended hiatus, the BITKRAFT annual summit returned September 19-20, 2022, with over 400 investors, entrepreneurs, strategic partners, and high-profile speakers convening at Chelsea Factory in New York City.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Venture Capital"}],"insightType":{"name":"Video","pluralName":"Videos"},"publishDate":"2023-03-16","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"a-lucid-look-at-the-state-of-ar-technology","title":"A Lucid Look at The State of AR Technology","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008210-snap_snapfest_food-menu_bw.jpg?auto=format","width":1920,"height":1080,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>In October last year, we shared our Perspectives on Extended Reality — an umbrella term by which we encompass Augmented, Mixed, and Virtual Reality. Much has happened since then. From Apple reportedly working on an AR/VR “reality OS,” to Qualcomm introducing a wireless version of its Smart Viewer headset, to Google now testing prototypes in public, the AR race is officially on. This presents us with the perfect opportunity to follow up with a dedicated deep dive on the state of Augmented Reality (AR).</p>","topics":[{"name":"Immersive Technology"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-15","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"assessing-blockchain-gaming-s-environmental-impact-and-what-can-be-done-about-it","title":"Assessing Blockchain Gaming’s Environmental Impact — and What Can Be Done About It Today","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008314-blockchain-environment_header_bw.png?auto=format","width":1200,"height":600,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"If you follow the crypto space even remotely, you may have seen one particular topic come up a lot in recent months: the environment. Though cryptocurrencies are no strangers to ecological controversy, the sudden rise of NFTs and the attempt of a number of gaming publishers to implement them inside their properties have brought new grist to the mill of the cryptosceptic crowd.","topics":[{"name":"Immersive Technology"},{"name":"Gaming"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-14","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"bitkraft-green-initiative-008000","title":"BITKRAFT Green Initiative #008000","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008396-trees_final_bw.jpeg?auto=format","width":1600,"height":1067,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"There is an increasing need for each of us to act more directly in accordance with the world we envision. It is not enough to merely hope that others will do the work we know is necessary to advance progress towards a better future.This is true certainly for each of us as individuals, but especially true for those who feel a sense of responsibility for embodying responsible entrepreneurship and for making an outsized impact, as we do at BITKRAFT.","topics":[],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-13","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"how-ai-is-helping-build-and-humanize-virtual-worlds","title":"How AI is helping build, and humanize, virtual worlds","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008457-replika_features_bw.png?auto=format","width":1400,"height":788,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>Playing video games, it’s easy to forget how much calculation is actually running in the background to produce what you’re seeing. Everything from a game’s physics to its lighting&nbsp;and terrain is the result of some carefully programmed computation — gaming companies can be some of the most complex software companies out there.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Immersive Technology"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-10","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}},{"slug":"infrastructure-the-future-of-a-decentralized-web","title":"Infrastructure & the Future of a Decentralized Web","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 2104px) 100vw, 2104px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008527-untitled-6.jpg?auto=format","width":2104,"height":1172,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"<p>A few months ago, we wrote an Insights piece that explored how gaming could potentially drive greater adoption of decentralized blockchain technology. While it’s still early, signs suggest this thesis is playing out. According to DappRadar, blockchain gaming activity is accelerating and gaining a greater share of user activity across Web3 applications.</p>","topics":[{"name":"Web3"},{"name":"Immersive Technology"}],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-09","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}}}],"data":{"insightsDetailPage":{"copyLink":"Copy Link","linkCopied":"Link Copied"},"article":{"components":[{"__typename":"T010QuoteRecord","id":"160821300","author":"","quote":"“Trees are the world’s most promising carbon capture solution, with potential for immediate impact.”"},{"__typename":"M001ImageLargeRecord","id":"160821301","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1279px) 100vw, 1279px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685610571-62412e538d5dc25164a6dcc1_tf_website_pr_1279x580_bitkraft_v1.jpg?auto=format","width":1279,"height":580,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"caption":"","source":""},{"__typename":"T003ContentRecord","id":"160821302","title":"BITKRAFT’s #008000 Initiative and Partnership With Terraformation","copy":"<article id=\"post-9356\" class=\"post-9356 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-initiatives\">\n  <div class=\"inner-wrap\">\n    <div class=\"post-content\">\n      <div class=\"content-inner\">\n        <p>There is an increasing need for each of us to act more directly in accordance with the world we envision. It is not enough to merely hope that others will do the work we know is necessary to advance progress towards a better future.</p>\n        <p>This is true certainly for each of us as individuals, but especially true for those who feel a sense of responsibility for embodying responsible entrepreneurship and for making an outsized impact, as we do at BITKRAFT.</p>\n        <p>As such, and in-line with our expanding commitment to the greater social good, we are today announcing our #008000 initiative. Imbued in its ethos by the color green, the BITKRAFT Management company will devote financial resources and attention to projects focused on environmental impact and green causes. This initiative also sets the stage for the BITKRAFT Foundation, a dedicated non-profit vehicle which we are setting up to facilitate all our future environmental and social initiatives, also providing a framework for our Limited Partners, Founders and portfolio companies to participate in.</p>\n        <p>Our first #008000 commitment comes in the form of a reforestation partnership with Terraformation, a tech-accelerated forestry company focused on the restoration of biodiverse forests and seed banking.</p>\n        <p>Terraformation’s vision is to bring Silicon Valley’s techniques for rapid growth to forest restoration, as forests represent the most immediately available and effective means of carbon capture. Put most simply, Terraformation is addressing the largest bottlenecks to forest restoration at scale.</p>\n        <p>BITKRAFT’s financial investment in the work of Terraformation will help to underwrite two key projects:</p>\n        <p>ReClimate, Ukraine – an NGO founded by three women entrepreneurs that creates a sustainable model of forest management, bringing together local foresters and small businesses to maintain the restoration of the biodiverse forests in the Rivne region in Ukraine. To date, 300,000 trees have been planted, and the project has prevented over 100 forest fires in the last three years as well as created dozens of jobs to plant and protect the forest and supported the preservation of 80+ species of rare animals. BITKRAFT will be ReClimate’s first international sponsor, enabling the planting of 10,000 trees. This project was selected prior to Russia’s invasion of Ukraine, and both Terraformation and BITKRAFT are undeterred in their efforts to support ReClimate’s instrumental forest restoration work.</p>\n        <p>The Kilimanjaro Project, Tanzania – a grassroots initiative activating community leaders and local partners to create a scalable restoration initiative around Mount Kilimanjaro, Tanzania, in East Africa. BITKRAFT’s commitment to supporting a reforestation seed bank will help the project’s goal of planting 10 million trees within the next seven years across 13,500 hectares, benefiting over 350,000 people while capturing millions of tonnes of carbon.</p>\n        <p>Though these project areas mark the beginning of our partnership with Terraformation, our BITKRAFT Foundation will cement our steadfast, long term commitment.</p>\n        <p>The transition to a more sustainable way of life will require a sustainable commitment not only from ourselves, but all who call our planet home.</p>\n        <p>To wit, beyond driving material outcomes in service of a greener tomorrow, our greatest hope for the work we do through #008000 is that it empowers our partners, stakeholders and portfolio companies to join us in collective action, and that it inspires similar engagement across our community and industry, as we know that meaningful progress in these areas will require the work of many.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</article>","button":"","url":"","openInNewTab":true,"fullWidthMobile":true}],"referenceTitle":"References","references":[],"slug":"bitkraft-green-initiative-008000","title":"BITKRAFT Green Initiative #008000","featured":null,"heroImage":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008396-trees_final_bw.jpeg?auto=format","width":1600,"height":1067,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}},"excerpt":"There is an increasing need for each of us to act more directly in accordance with the world we envision. It is not enough to merely hope that others will do the work we know is necessary to advance progress towards a better future.This is true certainly for each of us as individuals, but especially true for those who feel a sense of responsibility for embodying responsible entrepreneurship and for making an outsized impact, as we do at BITKRAFT.","topics":[],"insightType":{"name":"Article","pluralName":"Articles"},"publishDate":"2023-03-13","author":{"name":"BITKRAFT","image":{"responsiveImage":{"sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px","src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1689260023-favicon.png?auto=format&fit=crop&h=100&w=100","width":100,"height":100,"alt":null,"title":null,"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}}},"seo":[{"attributes":null,"content":"BITKRAFT Green Initiative #008000 - BITKRAFT Ventures","tag":"title"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:title","content":"BITKRAFT Green Initiative #008000"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"name":"twitter:title","content":"BITKRAFT Green Initiative #008000"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"name":"description","content":"BITKRAFT Ventures"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:description","content":"BITKRAFT Ventures"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"name":"twitter:description","content":"BITKRAFT Ventures"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:image","content":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008396-trees_final_bw.jpeg?auto=format&fit=max&w=1200"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:image:width","content":"1200"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:image:height","content":"800"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"name":"twitter:image","content":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/98662/1685008396-trees_final_bw.jpeg?auto=format&fit=max&w=1200"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:locale","content":"en"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:type","content":"article"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"og:site_name","content":"BITKRAFT Ventures"},"content":null,"tag":"meta"},{"attributes":{"property":"article:modified_time","content":"2023-06-27T13:13:00Z"},"content":nul